    "free_text":{
      "Learning outcomes":"The course provides an overview of the fundamentals of magnetic confinement of plasmas for fusion. The different magnetic confinement configurations are presented, with a description of their operating regimes. [br/]The basic elements of particle and energy transport are introduced. Finally, the plasma heating techniques are addressed.[br/]The course aims at providing both an experimental and a theoretical approach to the subjects. The introductory plasma physics courses are a pre-requisite.[br/]",
      "Content":"The course will consist of three parts:[br/]- an overview of the different magnetic confinement configurations (tokamaks, stellarator, RFPs, ...) and of the operating regimes (L mode, H mode, ...), with an introduction to the plasma-wall interaction (5 lectures);[br/]- introduction to particle and energy transport in magnetic confinement devices (classical, neoclassical, and turbulent transport) (6 lectures); [br/]- basic principles of plasma heating and current drive, including heating due to fusion-generated alpha particles (3 lectures). [br/]",
      "Required prior knowledge":"Basic plasma physics courses"
